text: The 2014 Hayne/Mannah Cup was a rugby league test match played between Fiji and Lebanon. ==Background== The fixture was in honour of Parramatta Eels players, Jarryd Hayne and Tim Mannah, who both have Fijian and Lebanese heritage respectively. Fiji won the test match by 40-28 after leading 22-12 at half- time.http://www.parraeels.com.au/news/2014/10/20/fiji_outmuscle_lebanon_in_hayne_mannah_cup.html Fiji's James Storer won the man of the match award, scoring one try in the match. ==Squads== ===Fiji=== *Coach: Rick Stone {| class="wikitable" |- bgcolor=#bdb76b !
